Web Application

Summary

ResourceMethodDescription
http://localhost:8080/peregrineapi/../api/4.0/IfdConceptGET

POST

 Gets the paged list of all IfdConcepts. Will return the list with up to 100 elements, or lower if specified. If page is specified it will return the list from the page You need minimum IFD_ADMINISTRATOR access to use this method. Undocumented API

Creates a new concept in bsDD Names and descriptions must be existing or be added before a new concept can be added. As a minimum a name in international English and another language must be provided. You need minimum IFD_EDITOR access to use this method.

http://localhost:8080/peregrineapi/../api/4.0/IfdConcept/listGET

 Gets a list of concepts from a list of global unique identifiers (GUIDs). If GUIDs for concepts that has been merged is provided then the new merged concepts is returned different GUIDs. No error message is given. Software should therefore test the provided GUID against the returned GUID to check if the original concept has been merged. You need minimum IFD_READ_AND_COMMENT access to use this method.
http://localhost:8080/peregrineapi/xml/IfdConcept/listGET

 Gets a list of concepts from a list of global unique identifiers (GUIDs). If GUIDs for concepts that has been merged is provided then the new merged concepts is returned different GUIDs. No error message is given. Software should therefore test the provided GUID against the returned GUID to check if the original concept has been merged. You need minimum IFD_READ_AND_COMMENT access to use this method.
http://localhost:8080/peregrineapi/json/IfdConcept/listGET

 Gets a list of concepts from a list of global unique identifiers (GUIDs). If GUIDs for concepts that has been merged is provided then the new merged concepts is returned different GUIDs. No error message is given. Software should therefore test the provided GUID against the returned GUID to check if the original concept has been merged. You need minimum IFD_READ_AND_COMMENT access to use this method.
http://localhost:8080/peregrineapi/../api/4.0/IfdConcept/searchPOST

 This function uses POST instead of GET
Search for a concept in bSDD by a search string consisting with a minimum length of 1 character. The search string must be provided in UTF-8 format and only * is allowed as wildcard characters. You can search using * in the end of a sentence not inside or in the beginning. The API will search full-names, short-names for the given string. Will return a paged list with up to 100 elements, or lower if specified. If page is specified it will return the list from the page You need minimum PUBLIC access to use this method.
http://localhost:8080/peregrineapi/xml/IfdConcept/searchPOST

 This function uses POST instead of GET

You can search using * in the end of a sentence not inside or in the beginning. The API will search full-names, short-names for the given string. Will return a paged list with up to 100 elements, or lower if specified. If page is specified it will return the list from the page You need minimum PUBLIC access to use this method.

http://localhost:8080/peregrineapi/../api/4.0/IfdConcept/searchForDuplicatesPOST

 This method tries to list candidates that could be possible duplicates of concepts for which the list of names given, belongs. There is always a chance that a concept not returned here might still be a duplicate. The list returned here is not necessarily exhaustive. You need minimum PUBLIC access to use this method.
http://localhost:8080/peregrineapi/xml/IfdConcept/searchForDuplicatesPOST

There is always a chance that a concept not returned here might still be a duplicate. The list returned here is not necessarily exhaustive. You need minimum PUBLIC access to use this method.

http://localhost:8080/peregrineapi/../api/4.0/IfdConcept/{guid}GET

DELETE

 Gets one concept from its global unique identifier (GUID). If a GUID for a concept that has been merged is provided then the new merged concept is returned with a different GUID. No error message is given. Software should therefore test the provided GUID against the returned GUID to check if the original concept has been merged. You need minimum PUBLIC access to use this method.

Removes the concept from the buildingSMART Data Dictionary. You need minimum IFD_ADMINISTRATOR access to use this method. Undocumented API

http://localhost:8080/peregrineapi/../api/4.0/IfdContext/currentUserCanEditGET

 Gets the list of contexts in bSDD that the current user can edit You need minimum IFD_READ_ONLY access to use this method. isReadOnly = true: only owners can add to and edit this context isReadOnly = false: both owners and users can add to and edit this context isRestricted = true: only users and owners can see and filter by this context, isRestricted = false: anyone can see and filter by this context

http://localhost:8080/peregrineapi/../api/4.0/IfdContext/{guid}GET

PUT

DELETE

 Gets the the context object with the given GUID. You need minimum IFD_READ_ONLY access to use this method.

Update the given context object. All parameters must be supplied. To leave an attribute unchanged, supply the content of the original attribute. You need minimum IFD_EDITOR access to use this method, AND you need to be in the Owners list of this context.

Removes the given context. You need minimum IFD_EDITOR access to use this method, AND you need to be in the Owners list of this context.

http://localhost:8080/peregrineapi/../api/4.0/IfdConcept/preferred/listGET

 Gets a list of concepts from a list of global unique identifiers (GUIDs), with only preferred names/descriptions/illustrations attached. Names/descriptions/illustrations attached to the concepts that is not preferred by the organization of the calling user will not be returned. If GUIDs for concepts that has been merged is provided then the new merged concepts is returned different GUIDs. No error message is given. Software should therefore test the provided GUID against the returned GUID to check if the original concept has been merged. You need minimum IFD_READ_AND_COMMENT access to use this method.

http://localhost:8080/peregrineapi/../api/4.0/IfdConcept/search/{searchString}GET

 Search for a concept in bSDD by a search string consisting with a minimum length of 1 character. The search string must be provided in UTF-8 format and only * is allowed as wildcard characters. You can search using * in the end of a sentence not inside or in the beginning. The API will search full-names, short-names for the given string. Will return a paged list with up to 100 elements, or lower if specified. If page is specified it will return the list from the page You need minimum PUBLIC access to use this method.

http://localhost:8080/peregrineapi/../api/4.0/IfdSandboxConcept/{sandboxGuid}/{guid}GET

DELETE

 Gets the sandbox concept with the given GUID. You need minimum IFD_READ_ONLY access to use this method, AND you need to have proper access rights to the sandbox it belongs to.

Removes the the sandbox concept. This also removes all data attached to this concept, e.g names, that are not in use by other concepts! You need minimum IFD_EDITOR access to use this method, AND you need proper access to the sandbox where the sandbox concept belongs.

http://localhost:8080/peregrineapi/../api/4.0/IfdConcept/search/filter/language/typePOST

 This function uses POST instead of GET.
Search with language and type filter.
Search for a concept in bSDD by a search string consisting with a minimum length of 1 character, and with the additional filtering on both language and concept type. The search string must be provided in UTF-8 format and only * is allowed as wildcard characters. You can search using * in the end of a sentence not inside or in the beginning. The API will search full-names, short-names for the given string. You need minimum PUBLIC access to use this method.

http://localhost:8080/peregrineapi/../api/4.0/IfdConcept/searchForDuplicates/filter/type/{conceptType}POST

 This method tries to list candidates that could be possible duplicates of concepts for which the list of names given, belongs. There is always a chance that a concept not returned here might still be a duplicate. The list returned here is not necessarily exhaustive. The list is filtered on the given concept type. You need minimum PUBLIC access to use this method.

http://localhost:8080/peregrineapi/../api/4.0/IfdConcept/search/filter/language/{languageGuid}/{searchString}GET

 * Search with language filter.
Search for a concept in bSDD by a search string consisting with a minimum length of 1 character, and with the additional filtering on language. The search string must be provided in UTF-8 format and only * is allowed as wildcard characters. You can search using * in the end of a sentence not inside or in the beginning. The API will search full-names, short-names for the given string. Will return a paged list with up to 100 elements, or lower if specified. If page is specified it will return the list from the page You need minimum PUBLIC access to use this method.

http://localhost:8080/peregrineapi/../api/4.0/IfdName/search/filter/language/{languageGuid}/nametype/{nameType}/{searchString}GET

 Do a filtered search for a name in bSDD by a search string consisting with a minimum length of 1 character. The search string must be provided in UTF-8 format and only * is allowed as a wildcard character. You can search using * in the end of the search string not inside or in the beginning. You need minimum PUBLIC access to use this method.

http://localhost:8080/peregrineapi/../api/4.0/IfdConcept/list

Methods
GET

Gets a list of concepts from a list of global unique identifiers (GUIDs). If GUIDs for concepts that has been merged is provided then the new merged concepts is returned different GUIDs. No error message is given. Software should therefore test the provided GUID against the returned GUID to check if the original concept has been merged. You need minimum IFD_READ_AND_COMMENT access to use this method.

request
query params
guids unspecified type a comma separated list of the global unique identifier for the concept

responses
status:
200 - OK -
representations
application/xml
application/json

http://localhost:8080/peregrineapi/../api/4.0/IfdConcept/search

Methods
POST

This function uses POST instead of GET
Search for a concept in bSDD by a search string consisting with a minimum length of 1 character. The search string must be provided in UTF-8 format and only * is allowed as wildcard characters. You can search using * in the end of a sentence not inside or in the beginning. The API will search full-names, short-names for the given string. Will return a paged list with up to 100 elements, or lower if specified. If page is specified it will return the list from the page You need minimum PUBLIC access to use this method.

request
responses
status:
200 - OK -
representations
application/xmlIfdConcept
application/json

http://localhost:8080/peregrineapi/../api/4.0/IfdConcept/searchForDuplicates

Methods
POST

This method tries to list candidates that could be possible duplicates of concepts for which the list of names given, belongs. There is always a chance that a concept not returned here might still be a duplicate. The list returned here is not necessarily exhaustive. You need minimum PUBLIC access to use this method.

request
responses
status:
200 - OK -
representations
application/xmlIfdConcept

http://localhost:8080/peregrineapi/../api/4.0/IfdConcept/{guid}

Methods
GET

Gets one concept from its global unique identifier (GUID). If a GUID for a concept that has been merged is provided then the new merged concept is returned with a different GUID. No error message is given. Software should therefore test the provided GUID against the returned GUID to check if the original concept has been merged. You need minimum PUBLIC access to use this method.

request
template params
guid unspecified type the 32 character global unique identifier for the concept

status:
200 - OK -

Methods
GET

Gets the list of contexts in bSDD that the current user can edit You need minimum IFD_READ_ONLY access to use this method. isReadOnly = true: only owners can add to and edit this context isReadOnly = false: both owners and users can add to and edit this context isRestricted = true: only users and owners can see and filter by this context, isRestricted = false: anyone can see and filter by this context

request
query params
page_size unspecified type
page unspecified type the cursor returned from the previous page in it's header parameter "Next-Page"

responses
status:
200 - OK -
representations
application/xmlIfdContext

http://localhost:8080/peregrineapi/../api/4.0/IfdConcept/preferred/list

Methods
GET

Gets a list of concepts from a list of global unique identifiers (GUIDs), with only preferred names/descriptions/illustrations attached. Names/descriptions/illustrations attached to the concepts that is not preferred by the organization of the calling user will not be returned. If GUIDs for concepts that has been merged is provided then the new merged concepts is returned different GUIDs. No error message is given. Software should therefore test the provided GUID against the returned GUID to check if the original concept has been merged. You need minimum IFD_READ_AND_COMMENT access to use this method.

request
query params
guids unspecified type a comma separated list of the global unique identifier for the concept

responses
status:
200 - OK -
representations
application/xml
application/json

If a GUID for a concept that has been merged is provided then the new merged concept is returned with a different GUID. No error message is given. http://localhost:8080/peregrineapi/xml/IfdConcept/preferred/{guid}

Methods
GET

Gets one concept from its global unique identifier (GUID), with only preferred names/descriptions/illustrations attached. Names/descriptions/illustrations attached to the concept that is not preferred by the organization of the calling user will not be returned. If a GUID for a concept that has been merged is provided then the new merged concept is returned with a different GUID. No error message is given. Software should therefore test the provided GUID against the returned GUID to check if the original concept has been merged. You need minimum IFD_READ_AND_COMMENT access to use this method.

request
template params
guid unspecified type the 32 character global unique identifier for the concept

responses
status:
200 - OK -
representations
application/xmlIfdConcept

http://localhost:8080/peregrineapi/json/IfdConcept/preferred/{guid}

Methods
GET

Gets one concept from its global unique identifier (GUID), with only preferred names/descriptions/illustrations attached. Names/descriptions/illustrations attached to the concept that is not preferred by the organization of the calling user will not be returned. If a GUID for a concept that has been merged is provided then the new merged concept is returned with a different GUID. No error message is given. Software should therefore test the provided GUID against the returned GUID to check if the original concept has been merged. You need minimum IFD_READ_AND_COMMENT access to use this method.

http://localhost:8080/peregrineapi/../api/4.0/IfdConcept/search/{searchString}

Methods
GET

Search for a concept in bSDD by a search string consisting with a minimum length of 1 character. The search string must be provided in UTF-8 format and only * is allowed as wildcard characters. You can search using * in the end of a sentence not inside or in the beginning. The API will search full-names, short-names for the given string. Will return a paged list with up to 100 elements, or lower if specified. If page is specified it will return the list from the page You need minimum PUBLIC access to use this method.

request
template params
searchString unspecified type the search string on UTF-8 format

query params
page_size unspecified type
page unspecified type the cursor returned from the previous page in it's header parameter "Next-Page"
cache unspecified type you will receive cached data unless value is "false"

responses
status:
200 - OK -
representations

http://localhost:8080/peregrineapi/../api/4.0/IfdName/search/{searchString}

Methods
GET

Search for a name in bSDD by a search string consisting with a minimum length of 1 character. The search string must be provided in UTF-8 format and only * is allowed as a wildcard character. You can search using * in the end of the search string not inside or in the beginning. The API will search full-names, short-names and lexemes for the given string. You need minimum PUBLIC access to use this method.

searchString unspecified type the search string in UTF-8 format

query params
page_size unspecified type
page unspecified type the cursor returned from the previous page in it's header parameter "Next-Page"

http://localhost:8080/peregrineapi/../api/4.0/IfdConcept/search/filter/language

Methods
POST

This function uses POST instead of GET.
Search with language filter.
Search for a concept in bSDD by a search string consisting with a minimum length of 1 character, and with the additional filtering on language. The search string must be provided in UTF-8 format and only * is allowed as wildcard characters. You can search using * in the end of a sentence not inside or in the beginning. The API will search full-names, short-names for the given string. You need minimum PUBLIC access to use this method.

request
responses
status:
200 - OK -
representations
application/xmlIfdConcept
application/json

http://localhost:8080/peregrineapi/../api/4.0/IfdConcept/search/filter/language/type

Methods
POST

This function uses POST instead of GET.
Search with language and type filter.
Search for a concept in bSDD by a search string consisting with a minimum length of 1 character, and with the additional filtering on both language and concept type. The search string must be provided in UTF-8 format and only * is allowed as wildcard characters. You can search using * in the end of a sentence not inside or in the beginning. The API will search full-names, short-names for the given string. You need minimum PUBLIC access to use this method.

request
responses
status:
200 - OK -
representations
application/xmlIfdConcept
application/json

http://localhost:8080/peregrineapi/xml/IfdConcept/search/filter/language/type

http://localhost:8080/peregrineapi/../api/4.0/IfdConcept/search/filter/language/{languageGuid}/{searchString}

Methods
GET

* Search with language filter.
Search for a concept in bSDD by a search string consisting with a minimum length of 1 character, and with the additional filtering on language. The search string must be provided in UTF-8 format and only * is allowed as wildcard characters. You can search using * in the end of a sentence not inside or in the beginning. The API will search full-names, short-names for the given string. Will return a paged list with up to 100 elements, or lower if specified. If page is specified it will return the list from the page You need minimum PUBLIC access to use this method.

request
template params
searchString unspecified type the search string on UTF-8 format
languageGuid unspecified type the language GUID for the language used as filter

query params
page_size unspecified type
page unspecified type the cursor returned from the previous page in it's header parameter "Next-Page"
cache unspecified type you will receive cached data unless value is "false"

responses
status:
200 - OK -
representations
application/xmlIfdConcept

http://localhost:8080/peregrineapi/../api/4.0/IfdConcept/search/filter/language/{languageGuid}/type/{conceptType}/{searchString}

Methods
GET

Search with language and type filter.
Search for a concept in bSDD by a search string consisting with a minimum length of 1 character, and with the additional filtering on both language and concept type. The search string must be provided in UTF-8 format and only * is allowed as wildcard characters. You can search using * in the end of a sentence not inside or in the beginning. The API will search full-names, short-names for the given string. You need minimum PUBLIC access to use this method.

request
template params
searchString unspecified type the search string on UTF-8 format
languageGuid unspecified type the language GUID for the language used as filter
conceptType unspecified type filter by one of the following concept types <a href="objects_ifdConceptTypeEnum.html">ifdConceptTypeEnum</a>

query params
page_size unspecified type
page unspecified type the cursor returned from the previous page in it's header parameter "Next-Page"
cache unspecified type you will receive cached data unless value is "false"

responses
status:
200 - OK -
representations
application/xmlIfdConcept
application/json
